---
// /brands/lincoln-pizza-oven-repair/, Cluster 09. Lincoln Foodservice Products, Fort Wayne IN. Welbilt→Ali 2022.
// Cross-cluster 301 target inheriting C07 /lincoln-commercial-ovens-repair/ (40 imp pizza-specific).
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Lincoln Pizza Oven Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Lincoln Impinger 1100/1600/2500 conveyor pizza oven repair Southern California. Welbilt→Ali Group. Chain OEM. $120. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/lincoln-pizza-oven-repair/";

const faqs = [
  { q: "Who owns Lincoln Impinger?", a: "Lincoln Foodservice Products has been part of Ali Group since July 2022, when Ali Group completed its acquisition of Welbilt Inc. (Lincoln's previous parent). Lincoln is headquartered in Fort Wayne, Indiana, and has manufactured commercial conveyor pizza ovens since 1958. The brand is NOT Lincoln Electric (welding equipment, completely different company despite shared name). Post-2022, Lincoln is an Ali Group NA sibling to Pitco and Frymaster fryers (cluster 06), Champion and CMA dishwashers (cluster 05), Manitowoc ice machines (cluster 03), Beverage-Air refrigeration (cluster 02), Kolpak/Master-Bilt/Nor-Lake walk-ins (cluster 01), Garland ranges (cluster 08), and Montague ranges (cluster 08). Ali Group 8-plus-brand family single-call service covers LA kitchens running multi-Ali configurations." },
  { q: "What's the Impinger technology?", a: "Impinger is Lincoln's signature air-flow conveyor technology, focused jet airflow directed perpendicular to the pizza surface through distribution nozzles in the oven chamber. The impingement approach cooks faster and more uniformly than simple radiant-heat conveyor designs, and distinguishes Lincoln conveyors from competitor Middleby Marshall PS/WOW conveyors at the engineering level. Impinger is Lincoln technology, not a separate brand. Models: 1100 countertop conveyor, 1600/1620 mid-size, 2500/2501 full-size, 3000 series high-volume. Each size operates the same Impinger airflow principle at different throughput capacities." },
  { q: "Lincoln vs Middleby Marshall, which to choose?", a: "Both are leading commercial pizza conveyor oven brands with comparable market positions; the choice for LA operators usually follows parts-chain preference and franchise spec. Middleby Marshall is the OEM standard across Domino's, Pizza Hut, Papa John's, Little Caesars, and most major US chain pizza franchises, if you're operating any of those franchises, Middleby Marshall is non-negotiable per corporate spec. Lincoln Impinger serves the independent pizza restaurant market plus non-Middleby chain operations. Engineering-wise: Middleby Marshall WOW offers bi-directional air-flow (more complex); Lincoln Impinger offers focused-jet airflow (simpler mechanically). Parts chains differ, Lincoln routes through Ali Group NA Winston-Salem NC; Middleby Marshall through Middleby Chicago/Elgin. We service both equally; see our <a href=\"/brands/middleby-marshall-pizza-oven-repair/\">Middleby Marshall pizza oven page</a> for the OEM-chain competitor detail." },
  { q: "What's the Welbilt → Ali 2022 parts-chain integration status?", a: "Welbilt Inc. was Lincoln's parent company from the 2000s through July 2022. When Ali Group completed the Welbilt acquisition in July 2022, Lincoln (along with Pitco, Frymaster, Garland, Montague, Delfield, Master-Bilt, Kolpak, Nor-Lake, and other Welbilt brands) transitioned to Ali Group NA's parts infrastructure at Winston-Salem, North Carolina. Integration is substantially complete as of 2026, though a small subset of specialty parts still route through legacy Welbilt channels with 5–8 day lead times. Common Lincoln parts (belts, burners, thermostats, ignitors) reach LA in 2–5 days via Ali NA distribution. Honest framing: the Welbilt → Ali transition was well-managed, but operators running 10-plus-year Lincoln units occasionally encounter specialty-part lead-time variance as legacy inventory works through the new supply chain." },
  { q: "What does Lincoln Impinger pizza oven repair cost in LA?", a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical Lincoln Impinger service ranges: thermostat $200–$340, conveyor belt tension $180–$320, burner ignitor $240–$400, gas valve $280–$480, impingement air-flow calibration $280–$480, high-limit reset $180–$320, conveyor belt replacement $380–$640, pilot / spark electrode $220–$380, end-panel / door gasket $200–$340, control board $700–$1,300, full burner refurbish $500–$820. Most Lincoln calls land $380–$780 parts-and-labor. Impingement-specific calibration and full belt replacement jobs run at the higher end. See our <a href=\"/price-list/commercial-oven-repair-cost/\">commercial oven repair cost guide</a>." }
];

const schema = { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@graph": [
  { "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business", "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair", "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/logo.png", "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/", "telephone": MAIN_PHONE, "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ] },
  { "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Lincoln Impinger Pizza Conveyor Oven Repair", "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" }, "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ], "description": "Lincoln Impinger conveyor pizza oven repair across Los Angeles, 1100 countertop, 1600/1620 mid-size, 2500/2501 full-size, 3000 series high-volume. Welbilt → Ali Group July 2022. Fort Wayne Indiana since 1958. Impinger signature air-flow technology. Ali Group 8-brand family single-call service." },
  { "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a.replace(/<[^>]+>/g, '') } })) },
  { "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [ { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" }, { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" }, { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Lincoln Impinger Pizza Oven Repair", "item": canonical } ] }
] };
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Lincoln Impinger down? Same-day commercial service:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>
  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap"><div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Lincoln Impinger Pizza Oven Repair</div><h1>Lincoln Impinger Conveyor Pizza Oven Repair</h1><p class="lede">Lincoln Impinger 1100 countertop conveyors, 1600 and 1620 mid-size, 2500 and 2501 full-size, and 3000 series high-volume, our techs service the full Lincoln Impinger commercial lineup across LA, Orange County, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. Welbilt → Ali Group family since July 2022; Impinger air-flow specialist service; Ali Group 8-brand family single-call; $120 diagnostic waived.</p><div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div><ul class="hero-facts"><li><b>Welbilt → Ali Group July 2022</b>, Fort Wayne IN; brand founded 1958, conveyor pizza specialist</li><li><b>Impinger air-flow technology</b>, focused-jet airflow distinguishes from Middleby Marshall PS/WOW competitors</li><li><b>NOT Lincoln Electric</b> (welding), different company despite shared name</li><li><b>Ali Group 8-brand family single-call</b>, Lincoln + Pitco + Frymaster + Garland + Montague + Beverage-Air + Champion + Manitowoc</li></ul></div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />
  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>Licensed BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day · 5 SoCal counties</span><span>$120 commercial diagnostic · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Lincoln Impinger, Welbilt → Ali, Fort Wayne IN since 1958</h2>
    <p>Lincoln Foodservice Products has manufactured commercial conveyor pizza ovens from Fort Wayne, Indiana since 1958, 67 years of continuous production. The brand pioneered the Impinger air-flow conveyor technology that's now standard across much of the commercial conveyor pizza oven market. In July 2022, Ali Group completed its acquisition of Welbilt Inc. (Lincoln's previous parent since the 2000s), integrating Lincoln into Ali Group NA alongside Pitco and Frymaster fryers, Champion and CMA dishwashers, Manitowoc ice machines, Beverage-Air refrigeration, Kolpak/Master-Bilt/Nor-Lake walk-ins, Garland ranges, and Montague ranges.</p>
    <p>Critical disambiguation: Lincoln Foodservice Products (commercial pizza ovens, this brand) is NOT Lincoln Electric (welding equipment manufacturer, Cleveland OH). The two companies share only the Lincoln name. When sourcing parts or scheduling service for a commercial pizza oven, specify "Lincoln Impinger" or the specific 1100/1600/2500/3000 model to route correctly.</p>
    <p>The Impinger technology is Lincoln's engineering signature. Rather than simple radiant-heat conveyor design, Impinger uses focused jet airflow directed perpendicular to the pizza surface through distribution nozzles in the oven chamber. The impingement approach cooks faster and more uniformly than basic radiant conveyor ovens, and distinguishes Lincoln engineering-wise from Middleby Marshall (the competing major chain-pizza conveyor brand, which uses different air-flow architectures including the bi-directional WOW oven system).</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Lincoln Impinger conveyor ovens we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>1100 Series, countertop conveyor</h3><p>Entry-size countertop Lincoln Impinger conveyor. Common at smaller pizza operations, independent restaurants, specialty food operations, and mobile catering setups. Service: belt tension, burner ignitor, thermostat.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>1600 / 1620 Series, mid-size</h3><p>Mid-size floor-model Lincoln Impinger conveyor. Common at mid-volume LA pizza operations and non-Middleby chain pizza franchise locations. Standard conveyor service pattern applies with scaled-up components.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>2500 / 2501 Series, full-size</h3><p>Full-size Lincoln Impinger conveyor for higher-volume operations. Common at LA independent pizza operations and some chain locations that specified Lincoln over Middleby Marshall. Service: full conveyor belt, drive motor, Impinger air-flow calibration.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>3000 Series, high-volume</h3><p>Lincoln's highest-throughput conveyor pizza oven line. Engineered for operations requiring sustained peak-hour pizza production. Less common than 2500-series in LA but present at specific high-volume independent pizza operations.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Impinger air-flow + common Lincoln service patterns</h2>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li><b>Conveyor belt tension</b>, Lincoln belts gradually slacken from continuous operation; tension-adjustment service 30–60 minutes. Full belt replacement 60–120 minutes.</li>
      <li><b>Burner ignitor assembly</b>, high-cycle firing wears electrodes over 2–4 year service windows. 45-minute service typical.</li>
      <li><b>Thermostat drift</b>, temperature control drifts affecting pizza cook consistency. Recalibration or replacement 30–60 minutes.</li>
      <li><b>Impingement air-flow calibration</b>, the signature Impinger technology depends on correct airflow distribution through the oven chamber. Blocked nozzles, fan-motor wear, or air-distribution-plate damage cause uneven cooking symptoms. Specialist diagnostic domain; requires Lincoln-specific Impinger training.</li>
      <li><b>High-limit reset failures</b>, safety thermostat trips under certain failure modes. Reset + root-cause investigation.</li>
      <li><b>Drive motor service</b>, conveyor drive motors wear over 5–8 year operation; bearing + brush replacement common at 3–5 year marks.</li>
      <li><b>Control board (newer electronic Lincoln units)</b>, parts from Ali Group NA Winston-Salem distribution, 2–5 day lead time typical.</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Ali Group 8-brand family single-call service</h2>
    <p>Lincoln's Ali Group ownership (since July 2022) puts it in the same family as a substantial list of commercial foodservice brands: Pitco and Frymaster fryers (cluster 06), Champion and CMA dishwashers (cluster 05), Manitowoc and Kold-Draft ice machines (cluster 03), Beverage-Air and True Refrigeration commercial refrigeration (cluster 02), Garland and Montague ranges (clusters 07 + 08), Kolpak/Master-Bilt/Nor-Lake walk-in coolers (cluster 01), and Delfield commercial refrigeration. For LA chain pizza franchise operations running multi-Ali configurations, common at independent pizza operations built with single-dealer Ali equipment packages, and at chain franchise locations that specified Lincoln, single-call service across the family delivers real operational efficiency. Shared Ali Group NA parts infrastructure at Winston-Salem NC; single service account.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Lincoln Impinger repair costs in LA</h2>
    <p>$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</p>
    <table class="price-table"><thead><tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical range (parts + labor)</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody><tr><td>Conveyor belt tension adjustment</td><td>$180–$320</td></tr><tr><td>High-limit reset service</td><td>$180–$320</td></tr><tr><td>End-panel / door gasket</td><td>$200–$340</td></tr><tr><td>Thermostat replacement</td><td>$200–$340</td></tr><tr><td>Pilot / spark electrode</td><td>$220–$380</td></tr><tr><td>Burner ignitor assembly</td><td>$240–$400</td></tr><tr><td>Gas valve replacement</td><td>$280–$480</td></tr><tr><td>Impingement air-flow calibration</td><td>$280–$480</td></tr><tr><td>Conveyor belt replacement</td><td>$380–$640</td></tr><tr><td>Full burner refurbish</td><td>$500–$820</td></tr><tr><td>Control board replacement</td><td>$700–$1,300</td></tr></tbody></table>
    <p class="small">Most Lincoln calls land $380–$780 parts-and-labor. Impingement calibration and belt-replacement jobs run at the higher end. See our <a href="/price-list/commercial-oven-repair-cost/">commercial oven repair cost guide</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Lincoln and Ali Group family pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/"><b>Commercial pizza oven repair Los Angeles</b></a>, service hub</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/middleby-marshall-pizza-oven-repair/">Middleby Marshall pizza oven repair</a>, direct conveyor competitor; chain pizza OEM</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/bakers-pride-pizza-oven-repair/">Bakers Pride pizza oven repair</a>, deck oven alternative</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/pitco-fryer-repair/">Pitco fryer repair</a>, Ali Group sibling (C06)</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/frymaster-fryer-repair/">Frymaster fryer repair</a>, Ali Group sibling (C06, McDonald's OEM)</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/garland-range-repair/">Garland range repair</a>, Ali Group sibling (C08, LA steakhouse standard)</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/commercial-refrigeration/beverage-air-commercial-repair/">Beverage-Air commercial refrigeration</a>, Ali Group sibling</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/manitowoc-ice-machine-repair/">Manitowoc ice machine repair</a>, Ali Group sibling</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow"><h2>Lincoln Impinger pizza oven repair, frequently asked</h2>{faqs.map(f => <details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>)}</div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap"><h2>Lincoln Impinger down? Call now.</h2><p>Same-day emergency response in LA, Orange County, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</p></div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
